planned, but never built.\n* M11, from the [[M1 motorway (Northern Ireland)|M1]] going through [[Lisburn]] and then crossing the M1 again and ending at [[Newry]]<ref name=\"Northern Ireland Roads Site\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wesleyjohnston.com/roads/historymotorwayplans.html|title=History - Northern Ireland Motorway Plans - Northern Ireland Roads Site|website=www.wesleyjohnston.com}}</ref>\n* M23, from the [[M2 motorway (Northern Ireland)|M2]] to [[Derry]]<ref name=\"Northern Ireland Roads Site\"/>\n\nThere were also urban motorway plans for [[Belfast]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wesleyjohnston.com/roads/belfasturbanmotorway.html|title=History - Belfast Urban Motorway and A12 Westlink - Northern Ireland Roads Site|website=www.wesleyjohnston.com}}</ref><ref name=\"Northern Ireland Roads Site\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of numbered roads in the British Isles]]\n*[[Motorways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n*[[List of controlled-access highway systems]]\n*[[Evolution of motorway construction in European nations]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n\n\n{{UK road lists}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Motorways In The United Kingdom}}\n[[Category:Lists of roads in the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:Motorways in the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:Roads in the United Kingdom|Motorways]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n[[File:UK motorways map 2016.svg|thumb|right|350px|'''UK motorways in 2016'''\n{{Legend-line|2px solid #7f99bf|M-designated motorway}}\n{{Legend-line|2px dotted #7f99bf|under construction}}\n{{Legend-line|2px solid #d0a3dc|Upgraded A-road designation}}\n{{Legend-line|2px dotted #d0a3dc|under reconstruction }}]]\nThe '''list of motorways in the United Kingdom''' is a complete list of [[motorway]]s in the [[United Kingdom]]. Note that the [[Great Britain road numbering scheme|numbering scheme used for Great Britain]] does not include roads in [[Northern Ireland]], which are allocated numbers on an ad hoc basis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.niassembly.gov.uk/qanda/writtenans/001215.htm |title=Northern Ireland Assembly \u2013 WRITTEN ANSWERS Friday 15 December 2000 |accessdate=2007-11-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081223010559/http://www.niassembly.gov.uk/qanda/writtenans/001215.htm |archivedate=23 December 2008 }}</ref>\n\n==Great Britain==\n\n===M-designated motorways===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=100%\n! width=\"49px\" align=\"center\"  rowspan=2| Link\n! class=\"unsortable\" rowspan=2|Route\n! class=\"unsortable\" rowspan=2|[[Ceremonial counties of England|Ceremonial Counties]] (England), [[Subdivisions of Scotland|Council Areas]] (Scotland) and [[Local government in Wales|Principal Areas]] (Wales)\n! rowspan=2|Highest junction to junction average daily vehicle flow 2018 <ref name=\"GB Road Traffic Counts\">{{cite web |url=https://data.gov.uk/dataset/208c0e7b-353f-4e2d-8b7a-1a7118467acc/gb-road-traffic-counts |title=GB Road Traffic Counts |accessdate=2019-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001163113/https://data.gov.uk/dataset/208c0e7b-353f-4e2d-8b7a-1a7118467acc/gb-road-traffic-counts |archive-date=1 October 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n! colspan=2 | Length\n|-\n! mi\n! km\n|-\n| [[M1 motorway|M1]]\n| The eastern north-south motorway linking London ([[Hendon]]) to [[Leeds]] and continuing north to the [[A1 road (Great Britain)|A1]] near [[Garforth]]. The first inter-urban motorway.\n| [[Greater London]], [[Hertfordshire]], [[Bedfordshire]], [[Buckinghamshire]], [[Northamptonshire]], [[Leicestershire]], [[Nottinghamshire]], [[Derbyshire]], [[South Yorkshire]], [[West Yorkshire]]\n|184,195\n|193.5\n|311.4\n|-\n|[[M2 motorway (Great Britain)|M2]]\n| From [[Strood, Kent|Strood]] to [[Faversham, Kent|Faversham]]. Bypasses the [[Medway Towns]].\n| [[Kent]]\n|99,450\n|25.7\n|41.4\n|-\n| [[M3 motorway (Great Britain)|M3]]\n| Main motorway from [[London]] to 